1.5 Normalizer¶

Normalizer1 $D_{Euclidean} = 1$ 1 3

NormalizerTF-IDFL2-Norm

Normalizer p-p-1

$${||x||}_p = (|x_1|^p + |x_2|^p + ... + |x_n|^p)^{1/p} $$

sklearnNormalizerp-norm${1, 2, \infty}$Normalizer

  • norm='l1': 1-${||x||}_1 = |x_1| + |x_2| + ... + |x_n| $
  • norm='l2': 2-${||x||}_2 = (|x_1|^2 + |x_2|^2 + ... + |x_n|^2)^{1/2} $
  • norm='max': $\infty$-${||x||}_{\infty} = max(|x_1|,|x_2|,...,|x_n|) $

Normalizer(norm='l2')

# TODO: 2. 
#

scaler = preprocessing.StandardScaler().fit(X_train)
X_train_scaled = scaler.transform(X_train)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)

scoresA = np.zeros([3,13]) # 
scoresB = np.zeros([3,13])

#

# TODO: 3. PCA

    pca.fit(X_train_scaled)
    X_train_pca = pca.transform(X_train_scaled)
    X_test_pca = pca.transform(X_test_scaled)

    # TODO: 4.MLP
    mlp = MLPClassifier(hidden_layer_sizes=[100,100], max_iter=2000, random_state=16)
    mlp.fit(X_train_pca, y_train)

    score_test = mlp.score(X_test_pca, y_test)
    scoresA[1, i] = score_train
    scoresA[2, i] = score_test
    print("n_components={0}:  {1:.4f} {2:.4f}".format(i+1, score_train, score_test))

print('')

from sklearn.neural_network import MLPClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
import time

start = time.time()

# faces.data/255[0,1]

import numpy as np
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3)
kmeans.fit(X_blobs)

#
x_min, x_max = X_blobs[:, 0].min()-0.5 , X_blobs[:, 0].max()+0.5 
y_min, y_max = X_blobs[:, 1].min()-0.5 , X_blobs[:, 1].max()+0.5
xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.arange(x_min, x_max, .02),  np.arange(y_min, y_max, .02))

Z = kmeans.predict(np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()])

Z = Z.reshape(xx.shape)
# 
plt.imshow(Z, interpolation='nearest',
           extent=(xx.min(), xx.max(), yy.min(), yy.max()),
           cmap=plt.cm.summer,
           aspect='auto', origin='lower')
# 
plt.plot(X_blobs[:, 0], X_blobs[:, 1], 'r.', markersize=5)

#
centroids = kmeans.cluster_centers_
plt.scatter(centroids[:, 0], centroids[:, 1], marker='x', s=150, linewidths=3, color='b', zorder=10)
plt.show()
